Former National Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Prince Uche Secondus, has declared that Atiku’s choice of the Delta State Governor, Ifeanyi Okowa, as his running mate, reflects his (Atiku) knack for choosing good heads to be around him for the difficult job ahead.
Secondus who noted that Okowa’s emergence completed Atiku’s candidacy for the presidency, expressed the opinion that the PDP is now set for an inevitable return to the Aso Rock Villa come 2023.
Visibly, going by his statements, the former PDP Chairman appears to be convinced that the party’s presidential candidate has made the best choice, in choosing Governor Okowa as his running mate for the 2023 presidential election.


